Ministry of Health on Wednesday reported the recoveries of 424 patients.Death toll from the virus has risen to 1,614 after 10 patients succumbed in the last 24 hours. Confirmed Covid-19 infections in Kenya have increased by 394 from 5,752 samples tested in the last 24 hours, the Ministry of Health has said.
According to the ministry, the total cases of infection in the country now stands at 92,853.
From the new cases 367 are Kenyan, while 27 are foreigners. From this number 271 are male while 123 are female. 



